---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Jakob Neugebauer" activePage="home">
  <div class="home-header">
    <div class="home-header-text">
      <h1 class="home-headline">AI Systems<br />& Data Infrastructure</h1>
      <p class="home-name">Jakob Neugebauer</p>
      <p class="home-role">Independent AI Systems Builder</p>
    </div>
    <div class="home-headshot">
      <img src="/images/headshot.jpg" alt="Jakob Neugebauer" class="home-headshot-img" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="home-intro">
    <p>
      Most organizations sit on large amounts of messy data.
    </p>
    <p>
      Contracts, registries, internal documents, financial filings – valuable information buried in <strong>PDFs, spreadsheets, and manual workflows</strong> that someone, somewhere maintains.
    </p>
    <p>
      I build the systems that replace that manual work. <strong>Automated pipelines</strong> that extract, classify, and structure information – <strong>no human in the loop where none is needed</strong>. What used to take a team now runs on its own.
    </p>
    <p>
      Where that automation runs depends on the constraints. When <strong>data sensitivity, cost, or regulatory requirements</strong> enter the picture, the architecture starts to matter – from cloud inference to <strong>local models</strong> to <strong>hybrid setups</strong> that keep sensitive data where it belongs.
    </p>
    <p>
      The model itself is usually the easy part. Choosing the right one is less so. But the real work is in <strong>pipelines, validation layers, infrastructure</strong>, and the kind of system design that keeps things predictable once they leave the demo environment.
    </p>
    <p>
      I am based in Vienna. My background is in Economics (WU Wien), International Management (Bocconi University), and Information &amp; Communication Systems (FH Technikum Wien, completed while working full-time). I have worked across startup, corporate, and consulting environments.
    </p>
    <p>
      I write about some of what I build in the <a href="/notes">Notes</a> section. If any of this sounds relevant, <a href="/lets-talk">let's talk</a>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="home-links">
    <a href="#" onclick="window.scrollTo({top:0,behavior:'smooth'});return false;">About</a>
    <a href="/notes">Notes</a>
    <a href="/lets-talk">Let's Talk</a>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
